# Supervised Learning Report

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates the implementation of supervised learning algorithms using Python and Scikit-learn. The objective is to understand regression and classification techniques by training and evaluating different machine learning models.

## Algorithms Implemented

###  1. Linear Regression
- Dataset: California Housing Dataset
- Task: Regression
- Evaluation Metrics:
  - Mean Squared Error (MSE)
  - R² Score

###  2. Logistic Regression
- Dataset: Iris Dataset
- Task: Classification
- Evaluation Metrics:
  - Accuracy
  - Precision
  - Recall
  - Confusion Matrix

###  3. Decision Tree Classifier
- Dataset: Iris Dataset
- Task: Classification
- Evaluation Metrics:
  - Accuracy
  - Precision
  - Recall
  - Confusion Matrix

## Results
- Linear Regression successfully predicted continuous house prices using the California Housing dataset.
- Logistic Regression achieved high classification accuracy on the Iris dataset.
- Decision Tree Classifier also performed effectively and was compared with Logistic Regression using standard evaluation metrics.

## Conclusion
This project provided practical experience with supervised learning algorithms. Linear Regression was used for predicting continuous values, while Logistic Regression and Decision Tree were used for 
classification tasks. Model performance was evaluated using appropriate metrics, demonstrating the strengths of each algorithm for different machine learning problems.
